idea about being more savvy

00:04:11.367 --> 00:04:12.767
about business and stuff
like that

00:04:12.767 --> 00:04:15.734
'cause I was losing money
from them all the time.

00:04:15.734 --> 00:04:17.400
[laughing]

00:04:17.400 --> 00:04:23.567
Eric: And so, uh, that was my
little free business school

00:04:23.567 --> 00:04:26.633
and so they gave me
the idea of --

00:04:26.633 --> 00:04:34.266
they -- they sort of created my
taste for the business world

00:04:34.266 --> 00:04:37.433
thinking -- they got me
thinking about branding and,

00:04:37.433 --> 00:04:39.266
you know, a lot of the things that I'm sure

00:04:39.266 --> 00:04:43.066
you all are experts in
or very familiar with.

00:04:43.066 --> 00:04:45.867
Niche, stuff like that.

00:04:45.867 --> 00:04:49.967
And so took a little time
from the jazz scene

00:04:49.967 --> 00:04:52.400
and tried to figure out
what it is I wanted to do

00:04:52.400 --> 00:04:55.800
and then I discovered alternative rock.

00:04:55.800 --> 00:04:59.834
I was so into the jazz world
and so into the whole concept of

00:04:59.834 --> 00:05:01.533
being a purist and
these kinda things

00:05:01.533 --> 00:05:03.333
that I never listened to rock

00:05:03.333 --> 00:05:09.300
and, uh, that's
the irony of it all.

00:05:09.300 --> 00:05:10.800
When I started hearing
some of the lyrics

00:05:10.800 --> 00:05:11.867
some of these rock tunes

00:05:11.867 --> 00:05:14.233
and what they conveyed,
what they expressed politically,

00:05:14.233 --> 00:05:16.700
and also just internally I was,

00:05:16.700 --> 00:05:18.533
like, wow, this is exactly
what I want.

00:05:18.533 --> 00:05:20.100
And also there was a lot
of relationship

00:05:20.100 --> 00:05:22.700
between the electric guitar
techniques and sounds

00:05:22.700 --> 00:05:25.000
and the piano techniques
and sounds 

00:05:25.000 --> 00:05:27.400
and I decided to try to
explore that a little more

00:05:27.400 --> 00:05:29.667
radically than had been done.

00:05:29.667 --> 00:05:33.767
So I saw an opportunity to
integrate my niche mentality

00:05:33.767 --> 00:05:37.667
that I got from my chess guys
and the powerful playing

00:05:37.667 --> 00:05:39.133
that I got from Elvin Jones,

00:05:39.133 --> 00:05:42.266
and the classical training
and stuff like that from home,

00:05:42.266 --> 00:05:44.000
and all my world
experience in jazz

00:05:44.000 --> 00:05:45.967
would improvising, all that.

00:05:45.967 --> 00:05:48.467
Put it all together,
I called it rock jazz.

00:05:48.467 --> 00:05:52.967
I play tunes that really
send me on the inside and,

00:05:52.967 --> 00:05:56.300
uh, I think that's it.

